any, one that=E2=80=99s driving into direct lending, structured credit and =
more, powered by Rowan=E2=80=99s financial masterstroke, the insurance arm =
Athene.
At the same time, Rowan is also chasing a more elusive goal, and one that=
=E2=80=99s difficult to quantify in dollars and cents. He wants Apollo to s=
hake off its image as one of Wall Street=E2=80=99s most ruthless risk-taker=
s for good.
Executives have spent the past few years on what some competitors have snar=
kily called an =E2=80=9CApollo Apology Tour.=E2=80=9D Even now, they often =
start meetings with prospective clients by fielding questions about their r=
eputation as a hard-driving investor and are putting more effort into expla=
ining their business, Apollo insiders say. =E2=80=A6
=E2=80=9CIt is up to us now, over this next period of time, to actually cha=
nge the perception for the reality of what the business is,=E2=80=9D Rowan =
said at the Economic Club of New York lunch. =E2=80=9CWe are primarily an i=
nvestment-grade provider of private credit.=E2=80=9D

If you build a reputation for extracting a lot of battle by being cleverer,=
 harder-working and more ruthless than everyone else, well, in large swathe=
s of finance that=E2=80=99s=C2=A0just=C2=A0good. Investors will want to giv=
e you money, because you are clever and ruthless. People will want to work =
for you, because they fancy themselves clever and ruthless, and because you=
 pay well. Creditors will fear you, which is not all good (you have to pay =
them more to finance your deals), but which is maybe helpful if you actuall=
y=C2=A0do=C2=A0end up fighting with them.
But if you are an investment-grade provider of private credit, that reputat=
ion is mostly unhelpful. If you=C2=A0go to an investment-grade company and =
say =E2=80=9Chey we would love to provide you with some investment-grade pr=
ivate credit=E2=80=9D and their first reaction is =E2=80=9Cokay but you pla=
n to kill us right,=E2=80=9D you will not get a lot of deals done. Lots of =
companies raise money from people who obviously plan to kill them, but that=
=E2=80=99s distressed credit and they have no choices; if you want to deplo=
y lots of capital doing investment-grade deals it is helpful to have a repu=
tation for being=C2=A0easy=C2=A0to deal with, not terrifying. If you=E2=80=
=99re an Apollo credit person, you probably do have to start every meeting =
by saying =E2=80=9Cno, I=E2=80=99m not like our private-equity guys, I=E2=
=80=99m nice, we sit on different floors, I=E2=80=99m scared of them too.=
=E2=80=9D

