<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One attraction of index investing is that nobo=
dy is responsible for any investing decisions. If I buy an index fund, I am=
 just following sensible standard financial advice about indexing and diver=
sification; if that index fund happens to hold stocks in companies that I f=
ind objectionable, I can say =E2=80=9Cwell that=E2=80=99s not my fault, I d=
idn=E2=80=99t buy <em>those companies</em>, I just bought the index fund.=
=E2=80=9D Meanwhile the index fund manager buys those stocks, not because s=
he wants to, but because they are in the index and her mandate is to track =
the index; buying those stocks is not really her fault either. Meanwhile th=
e index=C2=A0<em>provider=C2=A0</em>=E2=80=94=C2=A0the company that compile=
s the index and licenses it to funds =E2=80=94=C2=A0has some quasi-mechanic=
al standards for including stocks in the index, and they=C2=A0probably amou=
nt to something like =E2=80=9Cthis index includes all of the stocks in the =
market,=E2=80=9D or all of the biggest stocks, or all of the tech stocks, o=
r all of the US-based stocks, or all of the China-based stocks, or whatever=
 the index name says. There are indexes that are like =E2=80=9Cthis index i=
ncludes all of the stocks in the US that we do not find morally objectionab=
le,=E2=80=9D but that is more of a niche product than the indexes that are =
just all of the stocks.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And so in theory you can have a lot of ordinar=
y people investing their money in companies that they find objectionable, t=
hrough mutual funds whose managers find them objectionable, based on an ind=
ex whose compilers find them objectionable. Nobody=C2=A0<em>wants=C2=A0</em=
>to invest in those companies, but nobody is quite=C2=A0<em>responsible=C2=
=A0</em>for the decision, so they=C2=A0<em>do=C2=A0</em>invest in those com=
panies.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And, really, that is the point of indexing! Th=
e basic idea of index investing is something like =E2=80=9Cif you try to ma=
ke investing decisions they will be bad, so just buy the entire stock marke=
t,=E2=80=9D so it is important for index funds to be set up in such a way t=
hat nobody makes investment decisions. People=C2=A0<em>want=C2=A0</em>to ma=
ke investment decisions, but those decisions are bad for them, so you have =
to guard carefully against the tendency for investment decisions to creep b=
ack into the process. At every level, you want to make sure that no one is =
making decisions.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Of course this is exaggerated and we <a href=
